---

## The Epistemological Position

```
We are not saying: "Believe in this theory"
We are saying: "Apply these tests and observe"

If the theory is wrong:
  → The tests will fail
  → The predictions will not match
  → The constants will not appear

If the theory is right:
  → The tests will pass
  → The predictions will match
  → The constants will appear

Either way, YOU determine the outcome.
Using YOUR tools.
With YOUR observations.
```

---

## Key Insight

```
When you test the framework:
  → You are not "validating" it
  → You are EXECUTING it

The test IS the mechanism.
The mechanism IS the evidence.
The evidence IS the validation.

This is not circular.
This is self-demonstrating structure.
```

